1. Internal CSS Example:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <style>
    h1 {
      color: red;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>This is a Heading</h1>
</body>
</html>
      
op:
        This is a Heading



2. external CSS Example:

css
p {
  color: blue;
  font-size: 18px;
}
 html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>

         op:
            This is a paragraph.




3. inline css
<p style="color: green; font-weight: bold;">This is inline styled text.</p>

        op:
           This is inline styled text.


4. hr and br tag

hr:
<p>Above Line</p>
<hr>
<p>Below Line</p>
                    op:
                       Above Line
-------------------------
Below Line



<p>Hello<br>World</p>
                   op:
                      Hello
World
